# Project standards

- **Do not create markdown files** (README, docs, .md) unless the user explicitly asks for them.
- **Go**: Follow Effective Go. Run `make fmt` and `make lint` before considering code done. Use godoc comments for exported symbols.
- **Build**: After changing `api/design/*.go`, run `make generate`. The app uses Goa; generated code lives in `api/gen/` and repo-root `gen/` (both are built).
- **Tests**: Run `make test` (unit + integration). Integration tests need Docker; unit tests in `app/queryrunner/validator_test.go` must pass.
- **Commits**: Use Conventional Commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, style:, refactor:, test:, chore:).
- **Structure**: Application code in `app/` (config, db, queryrunner, metrics, llm, story, service, errors). API design in `api/design/`. Entrypoint `cmd/server/main.go`. Web UI in `web/`.
- **Database**: Allowed query schema is `demo`; read-only pool for queries, app pool for saved_queries/reports. Migrations in `app/db/migrations/`.
